  • Constructor Details

    • Main.HttpQueue

      public Main.HttpQueue(Main.HttpRequest... requests)
      Constructs an Main.HttpQueue with the specified HTTP requests.

      This constructor allows initializing the queue with one or more Main.HttpRequest objects, which are added to the queue upon instantiation.

      Parameters:
      requests - one or more Main.HttpRequest objects to be added to the queue. If no requests are provided, the queue will be initialized empty.

  • Method Details

    • processRequest

      public void processRequest()
      Processes and sends the first request in the queue.

      If a request is available in the queue, it is sent and then removed. If the queue is empty, a message is printed indicating no requests are available.

    • changeRequestPriority

      public void changeRequestPriority(Main.HttpRequest req, int priority)
      Changes the priority of a specific Main.HttpRequest and updates the queue order.
      Parameters:
      req - the Main.HttpRequest whose priority is to be changed.
      priority - the new priority value to set for the request.
